Body: Possible Duplicate:  How to move phone contacts to Google?  I am using my New Samsung Galaxy Y mobile phone.In My Contacts, I see that some are in SIM Memory, Some are in Phone Memory while others are in Google Accounts.In the Import/Export Option, I see Import/Export to SD card and Import/Export to SIM Card.I want to copy all my contacts in phone and sim memory to my Google Account. How do I do that? Is there any way to do it rather than doing it manually?
Title: Transfer all Contacts in Phone and Sim to Google Contacts
